verbose_text: Phosphocholine, the major product of choline metabolism in most cells (XREF_FIG C), did not displace specific [3 H] (+)-pentazocine from Sig-1Rs, and the other immediate products of choline metabolism, betaine (K i = 1.32 mM; pK i = 2.88 +/- 0.23; h = 1.40 +/- 0.35; n = 5) and acetylcholine (K i ~ 12 mM; n = 5), were less effective than choline.
